news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Ensure flawless land resurvey, officials told
news.para: The survey, conducted with the involvement of thousands of recruited people and by spending crores of rupees for purchase of modern survey equipment, should give no room for others to point fingers.

news.title: Tamil Nadu to explore chances of developing housing projects with Singapore
news.para: Our housing minister has informed me there are plans to promote couple of flagship housing projects in Chennai in collaboration with Singapore firms, said Palanivel Thiaga Rajan, minister for finance and human resource management, Tamil Nadu.

news.title: Coimbatore: It's time for new buildings to apply for property tax
news.para: The civic body had revised the property tax at the beginning of the current financial year based on the state government’s instructions.

news.title: Redevelopment of Dharavi: Pact inked for railway land in Dadar
news.para: Deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis, who was in Delhi for the meeting, tweeted that the development would pave the way for fast -tracking the mega project.

news.title: Six farmhouses built on Aravali land in Gwalpahari razed
news.para: The Supreme Court order had directed Haryana to restore the Aravali forest and to demolish structures that fall under special orders of Section 4 of the Punjab Land Protection Act (PLPA). No non-forest activity is permitted in the area.

news.title: Buyers knock Lokayukta's doors against incorrect orders passed by Karnataka RERA
news.para: “I request the honourable Lokayukta to investigate the letters, memorandums, and media publications to understand the struggles Karnataka home-buyers are undergoing due to ineffective functioning of K-RERA,’’ he said in the complaint to the Lokayukta.​

news.title: Aurum PropTech's revenue up 93.3% to Rs 28.3 crore in July-September 2022
news.para: Total income for the quarter also rose 96.2% sequentially to Rs 30.84 crore. Total income for the first half of 2022-23 rose to Rs 46.56 crore as against Rs 2.68 crore from a year ago.

news.title: Consumer panel asks Puravankara Projects to pay Rs 14 lakh to homebuyer
news.para: The developer was to hand over the apartment in March 2011. However, even after paying all dues, the apartment was not handed over, and the company demanded an extra amount of ₹4 lakh.

news.title: Lack of amenities in projects? Builders in Noida may face hefty fines
news.para: Currently, the Noida Authority seals the sales office or vacant units of the developer, imposes interest on due amount, or cancels the occupancy certificate issued to the developer. But, all these actions have more effect on buyers than developers.

news.title: ED starts probe into RERA scam involving 65 developers in Kalyan-Dombivli
news.para: Atleast 66 developers in Kalyan-Dombivli constructed illegal buildings in twin city and to sell flats prepared fake documents of building permission and using same documents obtained RERA certificates and later sold flats to buyers.

news.title: Two L&T firms eye 1.4 million sq ft in group's office park in Chennai
news.para: Earlier this year, L&T Realty pre-leased 600,000 sq ft for office space to technology firm Mindtree in its upcoming commercial office in Chennai. L&T could not be reached for comment. L&T is also in talks with CapitaLand to sell three towers spread across 2 million sq ft.

news.title: Uday Kotak looking to raise about $1 billion for a new residential real estate fund
news.para: Kotak Investment plans to complete the fundraising by the end of this year and to embark on its investment in 2023, focusing on residential property in India’s top five cities, a person familiar with the matter said. Deliberations are ongoing and details including size and investor lineup could still change, the person added.

news.title: Haryana RERA to pronounce order against ILD Millennium on Oct 27
news.para: ​The Gurugram bench of the Haryana real estate regulatory authority (H-RERA), observed that the developer has failed to complete its ILD Green group housing project in Sector 37C despite its repeated orders in the matter.

news.title: Axis Bank hikes MCLR rates across tenors by 25 bps
news.para: ​The country's third largest private sector lender in a communication on its website stated that the benchmark one-year MCLR is up by 25 basis points to 8.35 per cent with effect from October 18, 2022.

news.title: Lucknow divisional commissioner warns EESL to repair all street lights or face FIR
news.para: At a meeting to review the status street lights in the city, Jacob reprimanded officers of the LMC and the PSU. She said all the street lights of the city should either be changed or repaired within a week.
